# Master Rules — Lüdecker

Canonical doc: `docs/master_rules.md`. All decisions, implementations, and refactors must comply. If something conflicts, **the rules win**.

## Project context

| Area | Location | Responsibility |
|------|----------|----------------|
| Public site + CMS | `apps/website` | Next.js 15 App Router, routes, server actions, content queries |
| Design system | `packages/ui` | Figma tokens, CSS, presentational components |
| Shared types | `packages/types` | Content model, nav config, enums |
| Shared utilities | `packages/utils` | Slugify, dates, structured logger |
| Database | `supabase/migrations` | Schema, RLS, seeds |

**SSOT anchors (do not duplicate):**

- Site name, URL, contact email → `apps/website/lib/constants.ts` (`SITE_CONFIG`)
- Brand label in UI → `packages/ui/src/constants.ts` (`BRAND_NAME`, `CONTACT_EMAIL`)
- Design tokens → `packages/ui/src/tokens.css`
- Global + component styles → CSS files in `packages/ui/src/`, imported from `apps/website/app/layout.tsx` (never nested `@import` through package exports)
- Nav items, article types → `packages/types/src/index.ts`
- Published content → Supabase `content` table (fallbacks in `fallback.ts` only when DB unavailable)

## 1. Single Source of Truth (SSOT)

One truth per fact. Derived data is derived, never stored. No duplicate constants, state, or tokens.

## 2. Strong Separation of Concerns

- **UI** (`packages/ui`, layouts): render + interaction only
- **State**: transitions only, no UI
- **Domain** (`lib/content`, `packages/utils`): business rules, testable
- **Infrastructure** (Supabase, server actions, middleware): persistence + adapters

> If a file does more than one thing, it is doing too much.

## 3. Modular Design

Self-contained, predictable, replaceable modules. Explicit interfaces only.

- `packages/ui` must not import from `apps/website`
- `packages/types` / `packages/utils` must not import React or Next.js

## 4. No Hardcoding

Values come from `SITE_CONFIG`, env, constants, schemas, or state — not literals in components.

## 5. No Inline Styling

Token-based, class-based, centralized CSS only. No inline styles or style objects.

## 6. No Inline Components

Every component in its own named file.

## 7. Reusable by Default

Props in, no hidden context assumptions. Document intentional exceptions.

## 8. Logical Direction of Flow

Unidirectional: Input → State → Logic → Output. CMS: Form → Server action → Supabase → `revalidatePath`.

## 9. Explicit State Machines

Complex state (auth, forms, uploads) must have named states and explicit transitions.

## 10. Race Condition Avoidance

Async logic: cancellable, idempotent where possible, lifecycle-scoped. No stale closures.

## 11. Render Discipline

No unnecessary re-renders, no side effects in render. Prefer Server Components for public data fetching.

## 12. Predictable State Ownership

One owner per state. No mirroring across layers.

## 13. Validation at Boundaries

Validate CMS input and Supabase responses. Centralize schemas in `packages/types` and mappers.

## 14. No Hidden Side Effects

Side effects explicit and isolated. Server actions stay in `app/admin/actions/`.

## 15. Determinism Over Convenience

Same input → same output. Public pages stay SSG/ISR-deterministic.

## 16. Explicit Errors, Never Silent Failures

Log and propagate. Fallbacks only when documented, with logging first.

## 17. Naming Is Architecture

Intent-revealing names. Lowercase nav labels; editorial prefixes (`C:`, `P1:`, `A1:`) stay consistent.

## 18. Scalability Is a First-Class Concern

Design for growth and replacement. Clarity over cleverness.

## 19. Module Size Budgets

| Unit | Max lines | Complexity |
|------|-----------|------------|
| React component / hook | 250 | 15 |
| Next.js route file | 200 | — |
| Server action module | 250 | 20 |
| Domain / lib module | 300 | 20 |
| UI component + CSS | 250 | 15 |

Max **80 lines** per exported function; nested callbacks over **40 lines** must be extracted.

**Layer caps:** pages don't query Supabase directly; `lib/content` doesn't import UI; `packages/ui` doesn't fetch; types/utils stay runtime-free.

At **80% of budget**, extract before adding features. Run `fallow check_changed` when available.

## 20. Debug Logging

Use `@ludecker/utils` logger. Level + module + operation + context. Never log secrets. Every async op logs start/success/failure.

## 21. Testing

Unit, integration, and E2E coverage as appropriate. Behavior-focused tests; run in CI on every PR.

## 22. No Exceptions Without Documentation

Document why, alternatives, and safety before breaking any rule.

## 23. The Prime Directive

> Clarity beats cleverness. Predictability beats shortcuts. One truth beats convenience.

If something feels confusing, it is wrong.
